	<div class="widecolumn">

            <h2>LINKDATAGEN</h2>

            <p>Download <a href="linkdatagen.pl">linkdatagen.pl</a> Last updated 25/4/2009</p>
            <p>Download <a href="linkdatagen.doc">LINKDATAGEN documentation</a> Last updated 25/4/2009</p>
            <p>Download the annotation files.  These files are required by LINKDATAGEN and are generated by us from the (very large) Affymetrix annotation files and <a href="http://www.hapmap.org/">HAPMAP Phase I, II and III data.</a>.<br/>Download <a href="mappingfiles_affy_build36.tgz"> Affymetrix build 36 annotation files</a> Last updated 14/1/11.<br/>Download <a href="mappingfiles_affy_build37.tgz"> Affymetrix build 37 annotation files</a> Last updated 14/1/11.</p>
            <p>Download the test data set <a href="testdata.tar.gz">testdata.tar.gz</a> Last updated 13/3/2009</p>
	    <p>Linkdatagen.pl is a PERL script that generates LINKAGE style files for <a href="http://www.decode.com/software/">ALLEGRO</a> 
and <a href="http://www.sph.umich.edu/csg/abecasis/Merlin/index.html">MERLIN</a>, PREST, MORGAN and PLINK 
using as input the genotyping calls generated by BRLMM, Affymetrix annotation files, 
and a pedigree file. One of the assets of linkdatagen.pl is that it will allow the generation 
of LINKAGE files without having to use the Affymetrix GCOS software. For more details please refer to the <a href="linkdatagen.doc">linkdatagen documentation.</a></p><p>
</p>
            <p>Linkdatagen.pl can handle 50K Xba, 50K Hind, 250K Sty, 250K Nsp, 5.0 and 6.0 Affymetrix chip data.</p>

	    <p>Email bug reports & questions to Melanie Bahlo (bahlo@wehi.edu.au).</p>

            <p>If you use this program please acknowledge by citing:</p>

	   <p>Bahlo M, Bromhead CJ (2009). Generating linkage mapping files from Affymetrix SNP chip data. <i> Bioinformatics </i> 25(15):1961-2.  </p>

            <p>Last modified: 7-10-2005</p>

        </div>


